The paper discusses the use of functional dependence graphs in calculating network coding capacity bounds, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The concept of reduced FDG is introduced to reduce computational complexity, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the applications of reduced FDG in the algebraic formulation of scalar linear network coding, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
